![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/c7dfb94b-de6c-4919-a824-9c03f6b17d3b/20403.jpg)

PWInsider reports the angle on Raw earlier today with Bronson Reed and Bron Breakker turning on Seth Rollins happened because Seth Rollins was hurt at Crown Jewel: Perth over the weekend.

The belief is Rollins landed on his left shoulder when he hit the coast to coast headbutt

There is no official word on the nature of the issue, but Rollins was seen sporting a sling in a photo he took with a fan Sunday evening in Australia.

PWInsider reports he will be undergoing testing in the coming days.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/ac402082-0615-42d4-a070-1f55b494969d/20378.jpg)

Fightful reports sources in WWE hinted Bron Breakker and Bronson Reed attacked Rollins as a “heavy creative pivot” without being explicitly stated.

Fightful Select spoke to a source in WWE that indicated that they'd heard that a Bron Breakker split originally wasn't planned or in the cards until next year, somthing that Ibou from Self Made PW had heard previously.